Popular TV personality and ambassador, Rachel Bakam is dead Bakam, who hailed from Fadia Tudun Wada in Zangon Kataf Local Government Area of Kaduna State, died at 38. She died Tuesday afternoon at a private hospital in Abuja after a brief illness. Her younger brother confirmed the incident. Bakam was a prolific actress, writer, TV presenter and producer, and an anti-human trafficking ambassador. She was a peace and tourist ambassador. The media personality left behind a son.